    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focus on exploiting favorable matchups and speed differentials. Our strongest play is **Kyle Tucker** (77.16), whose elite profile is bolstered by a favorable matchup against Leiter (xERA 4.43). Close behind is **Jackson Merrill** (75.27), who benefits from a high-upside combination of a soft matchup, a park factor boost, and, most importantly, a slow pitcher delivery that significantly elevates his stolen base potential. **Gunnar Henderson** (69.67) remains a high-floor anchor; despite facing a tough arm in Webb, his leadoff placement and dynamic platoon advantage keep his efficiency high, though we are monitoring the 1.86s pop time of the opposing catcher as a subtle drag on his aggressive base-running upside.\n\nWe are prioritizing speed and matchup density, which led to the difficult decision to sit **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (50.63). While his base projection is robust, he fell just short of our efficiency threshold due to the rigorous matchup against Ryan and a structural focus on keeping our stolen base ceiling high. Meanwhile, **Nolan Schanuel** (60.15) earns a start today, capitalizing on the favorable matchup against the vulnerable Williamson (xERA 5.28). Risks are currently contained, though we remain cautious regarding **Drake Baldwin** and **Luis Robert Jr.**, both of whom face high-efficiency catchers today that may suppress their steal attempts despite their otherwise solid projected output. With **Coby Mayo** and **Josh Jung** falling below our 40.0 floor due to poor SP skill matchups and low lineup placement, the current configuration offers the optimal balance of efficiency and categorical scarcity management.",
